Manage User Groups

Manage groups menu gives access to:

  1. The list with all groups available in the system
  2. Options to deactivate and activate groups
  3. Create new groups

 

To deactivate a group use Deactivate action. The groups becomes inactive. All group members are no longer part of the group.

To activate inactive group use Activate action. The group becomes active.

To crate new group use Create group button.

For the group enter:

  • Title
  • Group id

Once the group is created you should assign the group a permission  (read the permission section of the guide).

 

 

To assign members to a group use Assign Members actions

To remove group members open the group in Edit mode and remove the users by selecting X sign next to the user name.
